'''Audio Frequency Modulation''' (AFM) is an [[audio recording]] standard used by [[VHS]] [[Hi-Fi]] stereo, [[8 mm video format|8mm]] and [[Hi8]] video systems. AFM is [[Monaural|mono]] on 8mm systems and [[stereo]] on Hi8.

